100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On February 7, 1926, a significant diplomatic effort unfolded as the League of Nations convened to address ongoing tensions in Europe, particularly regarding disarmament discussions. In the United States, the Senate continued its debate over the controversial Reed-Johnson Immigration Act, which aimed to limit immigration from certain countries. Meanwhile, the oil industry buzzed with news of a major discovery in Texas, promising to reshape the energy landscape.
